cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GR. 

The paper discusses a problem in computational geometry, specifically the problem of hinged dissections of polygons. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The problem also involves combinatorial structures and algorithms, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) as likely sub-categories. The problem may also involve graph theory and optimization, which are covered by cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
